        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Aug. 18. 1851</date></p>
			<p>Rev<lb/> <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dr. Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">I received your letter and<lb/> the proof sheets of my Manuscript this<lb/> morning&#44; and hasten to transmit it back<lb/> to you with a few slight corrections. All<add>&#63;</add><lb/> with my thanks for your promptness<lb/> and impartiality which you have evinced in<lb/> the matter.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Your letter explanatory of the insertion<lb/> of <persName>Mr. Newman&#39;s</persName> article is quite satisfactory.<lb/> Indeed your whole letter is so&#59; and reads<lb/> like the emanation of a good and just man.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You are mistaken as to the impression<lb/> imbibed here in consequence of your remarks<lb/> on the controversy about <persName>Mr Poznanski</persName> &#38; the <persName>Rev<lb/> Dr Eckman</persName>. If your argument is bad<lb/> in that matter&#44; it is because your premises<lb/> were rotten. And we found fault with<lb/> your drawing conclusions not warranted<lb/> by facts. But still the discussion was fair<lb/> and honorable&#59; gentlemanly and just. If<lb/> you do not convince your opponents you never<lb/> offend them. A spirit of truth and tolerance</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>seems to be your guiding star<add>&#63;</add> in all of<lb/> your productions. It becomes your character<lb/> and will keep you elevated as long as it<lb/> is exercised.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">With many wishes for your<lb/> welfare</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">I remain your obt. st.</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Isaac N. Cardilo</persName></p>
			<p>N. B. I perceive that you have<lb/> introduced the word &#40;wrangle&#41; in <persName>Mr.<lb/> Eckman&#39;s</persName> letter under the idea. I<lb/> suppose&#44; that it was an omission of<lb/> mine&#8212;but the original contained as&#45;<lb/>&#45;terisks as I sent it to you&#8212;altho&#39;<lb/> the context would <add>&#63;</add> the introduction of<lb/> the world &#8220;<hi rend="underline">wrangle</hi>.&#8221;</p>
          
        </body>
